<subSubSection id="11D26523454AB648B595FAEDFDE21B12" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="597736A8454AB648B595FAEDFDE21B12" blockId="9.[151,1437,1328,1643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454AB648B595FAEDFE8018EA" bold="true" box="[199,317,1400,1426]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454AB648B414FAEDFDF818EA" author="Dziedzielewicz, J." box="[326,581,1400,1426]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" pagination="13 - 25" refId="ref13945" refString="Dziedzielewicz, J. (1907) Sieciarki (Neuroptera genuina) i Prasiatnice (Archiptera) zebrane w ciagu lat 1904 i 1905. Sprawozdania Komisji Fizjograficznej Akademii Umiejetnosci w Krakowie, 42, 13 - 25." type="journal article" year="1907">Dziędzielewicz (1907)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<specimenCount id="4FCEFD21454AB648B7E0FAECFC9218EA" box="[690,815,1400,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
marked as 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B454AB648B6E1FAECFBFD18EA" box="[947,1088,1401,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Aulops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454AB648B6E1FAECFBFD18EA" box="[947,1088,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="468">P. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the vicinity of Mykulychyn village (Ukrainian Carpathians). The specimen was determined by F. Klapálek. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454AB648B108FA09FAE518CE" author="Dziedzielewicz, J." box="[1114,1368,1436,1462]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" pagination="38 - 40" refId="ref14051" refString="Dziedzielewicz, J. (1918) Owady siatkoskrzydlowate ziem Polski (Insecta neuropteroidea Poloniae terrarum). Rozprawy i Wiadomo s ci z Muzeum im. Dzieduszyckich, Lwow, 4 (1 - 4), 38 - 40." type="journal article" year="1918">Dziędzielewicz (1918)</bibRefCitation>
listed a few localities for this species within Gorgany and Chornohora Mountains. We did not find any specimens belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B454AB648B58DFA70FED61886" box="[223,363,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Aulops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454AB648B58DFA70FED61886" box="[223,363,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="468">P. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in SMNH collection for additional investigation, because material is lost (V.B. Rizun, 
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454AB648B068FA71FEF91B5A" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="468">personal communication</emphasis>
; collection curator at SMNH). However, the record is very probably based on misidentification with another species. 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454AB648B4DAF9B8FDE91B3F" author="Martynova, O. M." box="[392,596,1580,1607]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" pagination="721 - 747" refId="ref15684" refString="Martynova, O. M. (1957) Skopionnitsy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR. II Semeistvo Panorpidae. [Scorpion-flies (Mecoptera) of USSR fauna. II The family Panorpidae]. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 36 (3), 721 - 747. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1957">Martynova (1957)</bibRefCitation>
and later 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454AB648B793F9B9FC321B3F" author="Willmann, R." box="[705,911,1580,1607]" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref17174" refString="Willmann, R. (1978 b) Neubeschreibung der Typen von Panorpa caucasica Mac Lachlan, 1869. Bulletin de l'Institut royal des sciences naturelles de Belgique, 52 (9), 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1978">Willmann (1978b)</bibRefCitation>
knew 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B454AB648B68BF9B8FBD91B3E" box="[985,1124,1581,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Aulops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454AB648B68BF9B8FBD91B3E" box="[985,1124,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="468">P. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Caucasus only; no recent records of this species are known.
</paragraph>
